>bad_dead_coupler GOOD with R307A (arginine finger -> Ala) x6. Rationale: the trans arginine finger is the coupler that reaches into the neighbor ATP site; substituting it is the canonical AAA+ loss-of-coupling lesion. (Mechanistic context from ClpXP cryo-EM / review literature surfaced via search: eLife 52774, PMC9871882 — specific-claim attribution not independently verified in-session.)
